4 the sun was striking me on my right shoulder, 5 which, with its rays, was already changing all the west 6 into a white aspect from blue;
7 and I, with my shadow, made the flame 8 seem more ardent; and yet by that sign alone 9 I saw many shades, as we went, taking note.
